            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-12-27 11:24:14" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>a source of water flowing onto the surface or into a pool somewhat below ground level</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>spring</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>πηγή[a] spring differs from {L:φρέαρ&lt;SDBG:φρέαρ:000000&gt;}[a] and {L:πηγή&lt;SDBG:πηγή:000001&gt;}[b] well (see {D:7.57}) in that a πηγή[a] is normally a natural source of water, in contrast with {L:φρέαρ&lt;SDBG:φρέαρ:000000&gt;}[a] and {L:πηγή&lt;SDBG:πηγή:000001&gt;}[b], which are dug and into which a πηγή[a] may be said to flow.</Comments>
